{
  "name": "Wishlist",
  "description": "Customer wishlist surface (Sprint B4.4). 3 endpoints, all auth-gated to the calling customer.\n\n**Idempotency:**\n- `POST /wishlist/:tourId` upserts — re-posting the same tour is a no-op 200.\n- `DELETE /wishlist/:tourId` removes via `deleteMany`, so deleting an absent row returns 204 without error.\n\n**Pre-condition:** `{{tourId}}` env var points at a published tour UUID. Easiest source: copy the `id` field from `GET /tours/:slug` response.",
  "item": [
    {
      "name": "POST /wishlist/:tourId (add)",
      "request": {
        "method": "POST",
        "header": [],
        "url": {
          "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/wishlist/{{tourId}}",
          "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
          "path": ["wishlist", "{{tourId}}"]
        },
        "description": "Adds the tour to the caller's wishlist. Idempotent."
      },
      "response": [],
      "event": [
        {
          "listen": "test",
          "script": {
            "type": "text/javascript",
            "exec": [
              "pm.test('status is 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
              "const body = pm.response.json();",
              "pm.test('row contains tourId', () => pm.expect(body.data.tourId).to.be.a('string'));"
            ]
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "GET /wishlist/me",
      "request": {
        "method": "GET",
        "header": [],
        "url": {
          "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/wishlist/me",
          "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
          "path": ["wishlist", "me"]
        },
        "description": "Returns the caller's wishlist newest-first, with tour preview joined (slug, titles, hero image, basePrice, currency, durationDays)."
      },
      "response": [],
      "event": [
        {
          "listen": "test",
          "script": {
            "type": "text/javascript",
            "exec": [
              "pm.test('status is 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
              "const body = pm.response.json();",
              "pm.test('data is an array', () => pm.expect(body.data).to.be.an('array'));",
              "if (body.data.length) {",
              "  pm.test('row includes joined tour preview', () => pm.expect(body.data[0].tour).to.have.property('slug'));",
              "}"
            ]
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "DELETE /wishlist/:tourId (remove)",
      "request": {
        "method": "DELETE",
        "header": [],
        "url": {
          "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/wishlist/{{tourId}}",
          "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
          "path": ["wishlist", "{{tourId}}"]
        },
        "description": "Removes the tour from caller's wishlist. Idempotent — removing an absent row still returns 204."
      },
      "response": [],
      "event": [
        {
          "listen": "test",
          "script": {
            "type": "text/javascript",
            "exec": [
              "pm.test('status is 204', () => pm.response.to.have.status(204));"
            ]
          }
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}
